WEBVTT

01:36.930 --> 01:40.920
[The Best Thing]

01:41.430 --> 01:45.360
[Episode 5]
[Chinese Yam]
[It has a sweet taste and mild nature, strengthens the spleen and stomach,
generates fluids, and benefits the lungs]

01:47.039 --> 01:48.759
Look how delicious this is!

01:49.150 --> 01:49.710
Learn from it

01:49.710 --> 01:50.710
and cook for the two of us.

01:50.710 --> 01:52.430
Alright.

01:55.150 --> 01:55.920
What is that?

01:56.310 --> 01:58.400
Correct our work method.

02:00.560 --> 02:01.510
I'm back.

02:05.070 --> 02:08.979
Why are you two staring at me like that?

02:10.680 --> 02:11.770
Can't we look at you?

02:14.800 --> 02:15.750
Of course you can.

02:16.710 --> 02:19.030
Why do I feel like you're acting guilty?

02:21.870 --> 02:23.079
I'm not.

02:23.840 --> 02:24.710
Want a late-night snack?

02:25.000 --> 02:26.970
No, I need to go prepare the medicine.

02:32.280 --> 02:33.840
Don't you think she seems a little off?

02:33.990 --> 02:34.780
Weirdly suspicious.

02:35.510 --> 02:36.280
Not at all.

02:37.030 --> 02:38.400
She's doing great!

02:38.800 --> 02:40.430
Ever since she started taking traditional Chinese medicine,

02:40.430 --> 02:41.560
she's been more energetic and lively.

02:42.230 --> 02:43.280
Even when she said "No" just now,

02:43.800 --> 02:44.870
she sounded stronger than before.

02:45.240 --> 02:46.190
Are you dumb?

02:46.840 --> 02:47.400
Yes.

02:54.240 --> 02:55.400
I'm telling you,

02:55.400 --> 02:57.000
she must have gotten back together with Yan.

02:57.160 --> 02:58.350
She walks like the wind now.

03:26.030 --> 03:26.750
Thank you.

03:27.630 --> 03:28.750
How is it?

03:28.750 --> 03:30.870
This is the best seat in the house.

03:30.870 --> 03:33.150
I pulled some strings to get it.

03:33.560 --> 03:34.030
Right.

03:34.030 --> 03:36.240
Ms. Xu does have some impressive connections.

03:36.470 --> 03:37.750
Look, there are still empty tables behind.

03:38.630 --> 03:40.190
Ms. Xu, you should take us out more often

03:40.190 --> 03:41.360
so we can broaden our horizons.

03:41.360 --> 03:42.190
What's wrong with you?

03:42.190 --> 03:43.680
Those tables behind are clearly reserved.

03:43.680 --> 03:44.750
It's just that the diners haven't arrived yet.

03:44.750 --> 03:45.470
Oh, sure.

03:45.470 --> 03:47.000
Look behind me, this one's reserved too, huh?

03:47.000 --> 03:47.710
Hey, you!

03:47.710 --> 03:48.870
I have some mint candy.

03:48.870 --> 03:49.800
Do you want one?

03:55.750 --> 03:57.520
Since when do you eat mint candy?

03:59.240 --> 04:00.400
Dr. He

04:00.400 --> 04:01.840
recommended it to me.

04:01.900 --> 04:03.590
He said mint candy

04:03.590 --> 04:05.240
won't interfere with my TCM medication,

04:05.240 --> 04:06.030
so it's fine for me to have.

04:06.350 --> 04:09.100
Your handsome TCM physician is quite nice, isn't he?

04:09.520 --> 04:11.000
Does he know how to do massage

04:11.000 --> 04:11.750
and acupressure?

04:11.750 --> 04:13.430
Has he ever given you a massage?

04:13.870 --> 04:14.750
I don't know.

04:14.750 --> 04:15.630
I'll ask him for you next time.

04:16.850 --> 04:17.970
Speaking of this TCM physician,

04:20.010 --> 04:21.010
let me show you a video.

04:30.070 --> 04:30.830
Let me see.

04:33.190 --> 04:34.340
Oh, I've seen this before.

04:35.070 --> 04:35.870
It's gone viral.

04:38.170 --> 04:40.409
See? I wasn't lying.

04:40.480 --> 04:41.000
Doesn't he

04:41.000 --> 04:42.920
look a lot like that actor

04:42.920 --> 04:44.000
I told you about last time?

04:44.560 --> 04:45.480
The one from "My Journey to You"?

04:45.480 --> 04:46.310
Yes.

04:46.310 --> 04:47.750
He's really handsome.

04:48.200 --> 04:48.760
Xiangya,

04:49.240 --> 04:50.800
do you regret rejecting him

04:50.800 --> 04:52.430
so impulsively back then?

04:54.159 --> 04:55.040
Not really.

04:56.310 --> 04:57.310
He's not my type.

04:57.310 --> 04:58.310
He's too much of an old scholar type.

04:58.560 --> 05:00.410
No, he's not.

05:00.750 --> 05:02.680
I'm telling you, he's actually pretty fun to talk to.

05:02.680 --> 05:04.360
And he even skateboards.

05:04.380 --> 05:05.270
Not rigid at all.

05:07.390 --> 05:07.950
Well,

05:07.950 --> 05:09.800
why don't you give it a try?

05:10.390 --> 05:12.000
I really think you two are meant to be.

05:12.470 --> 05:14.040
You're both doctor and patient and neighbors.

05:14.040 --> 05:15.040
It's a double connection.

05:16.110 --> 05:18.190
I just broke up not long ago.

05:19.010 --> 05:20.650
But you seem to be doing really well.

05:21.240 --> 05:22.630
I slept through so many days at home.

05:22.630 --> 05:24.040
Of course I'm doing better now.

05:24.310 --> 05:25.070
No.

05:26.160 --> 05:28.720
I mean, after breaking up with Yan Heng,

05:28.950 --> 05:30.310
you're in a much better state than before.

05:34.580 --> 05:37.630
Dr. He and I are just ordinary friends.

05:38.600 --> 05:40.750
Then just start with being friends.

05:42.430 --> 05:43.190
Nope.

05:43.360 --> 05:45.750
Right now, I have zero interest in dating.

05:46.600 --> 05:48.409
There's really no need.

05:48.430 --> 05:49.750
You've already broken up.

05:49.750 --> 05:51.560
Why cling to a relationship that wasn't even worth it

05:51.560 --> 05:53.480
and ignore all the other possibilities waiting for you?

05:53.480 --> 05:56.190
I'm not ignoring the other possibilities.

05:56.530 --> 05:58.909
I think I'd rather invest my time in myself

05:58.940 --> 06:01.390
than spend it on a relationship right now.

06:01.390 --> 06:02.630
Didn't I tell you?

06:02.630 --> 06:04.240
I'm planning to study abroad.

06:04.240 --> 06:05.680
If everything goes well,

06:05.680 --> 06:06.830
by this time next year,

06:06.830 --> 06:08.360
I'll be in Switzerland.

06:08.560 --> 06:09.390
That means the only option

06:09.390 --> 06:10.800
would be a long-distance relationship,

06:11.220 --> 06:12.670
and now I know

06:12.690 --> 06:15.040
long-distance relationships just don't work.

06:22.990 --> 06:24.750
Do you think Xifan is interested

06:24.750 --> 06:26.430
in that handsome TCM physician?

06:28.340 --> 06:30.140
She seems to think highly of him.

06:30.660 --> 06:31.810
Should we try to set them up?

06:33.630 --> 06:34.870
But Xifan already said

06:34.870 --> 06:36.120
she doesn't want to date right now.

06:37.950 --> 06:39.630
That's just because she's focused on studying abroad

06:39.630 --> 06:40.750
and sees him as a friend.

06:41.270 --> 06:43.150
What if she realizes later and regrets it?

06:44.200 --> 06:45.200
That's true.

06:49.320 --> 06:52.030
Once you've been friends for a long time,

06:52.740 --> 06:55.150
it's hard to change that dynamic.

06:56.280 --> 06:57.080
Don't you think so?

06:59.390 --> 07:00.160
Friendships that have lasted a long time

07:00.160 --> 07:01.680
naturally have a hard-to-change dynamic.

07:10.460 --> 07:14.780
♫And you are the reason♫

07:14.800 --> 07:18.060
♫I hold on to the moment so dearly♫

07:19.110 --> 07:22.700
♫No fear of the night, no matter how long♫

07:22.800 --> 07:26.210
♫Your voice is always gentle♫

07:26.250 --> 07:30.400
♫Knowing you'll wait for me to take that brave step♫

07:30.420 --> 07:32.620
♫Walking toward you♫

07:32.800 --> 07:36.100
♫At the end of my dreams♫

07:36.210 --> 07:40.110
♫Holding on tight, never letting go♫

07:40.230 --> 07:43.810
♫Waiting for you♫

07:43.880 --> 07:47.330
♫To heal every tomorrow for me♫

08:07.920 --> 08:08.490
It's me.

08:09.330 --> 08:10.860
Do you have time to grab a meal?

08:11.630 --> 08:13.380
I have a flight back to North City

08:13.780 --> 08:14.650
this afternoon.

08:16.580 --> 08:18.380
I'm already eating. Maybe next time.

08:27.800 --> 08:28.610
Was it your dad?

08:31.320 --> 08:32.200
He asked me to have dinner with him.

08:34.679 --> 08:35.630
Are you going?

08:35.950 --> 08:36.539
No.

08:39.230 --> 08:40.280
Just to be clear,

08:40.559 --> 08:41.919
I'm not the one stopping you from going.

08:45.960 --> 08:46.920
I didn't plan on going anyway.

08:47.350 --> 08:49.040
There's nothing to talk about with him.

08:54.400 --> 08:56.440
Actually, you could go see him.

08:57.230 --> 08:57.990
Yes,

08:59.120 --> 09:01.590
he made mistakes in the past,

09:02.160 --> 09:03.750
but it's all in the past now.

09:04.920 --> 09:05.990
Maybe it's time for you

09:06.560 --> 09:07.970
to let go of the past.

09:18.750 --> 09:22.180
[13 years ago]

09:25.960 --> 09:27.560
Why do you still insist on studying TCM?

09:31.690 --> 09:32.690
I like it.

09:33.280 --> 09:34.320
I've told you before,

09:34.970 --> 09:36.490
you should study Western medicine

09:36.750 --> 09:37.990
and pursue clinical work,

09:37.990 --> 09:39.280
step by step.

09:39.280 --> 09:41.510
I've already paved the way for you.

09:41.800 --> 09:43.920
You just need to follow it,

09:45.200 --> 09:47.110
and you'll gain success and fame in the future.

09:48.320 --> 09:49.470
Success and fame?

09:50.990 --> 09:52.110
Like you?

09:56.320 --> 09:57.560
All these years,

09:58.350 --> 09:59.510
have you ever cared about me?

10:00.560 --> 10:02.080
When my mom was critically ill,

10:04.280 --> 10:05.040
where were you?

10:10.870 --> 10:12.230
And now, what right do you have to control me?

10:27.160 --> 10:28.180
Hello.

10:28.320 --> 10:29.830
Did you receive the project case

10:29.830 --> 10:30.990
I just sent you?

10:30.990 --> 10:31.960
If I score 7.5

10:31.960 --> 10:33.320
or above,

10:33.320 --> 10:34.710
wouldn't that help me more?

10:35.130 --> 10:36.320
Of course it would.

10:36.560 --> 10:38.450
A 7.0 meets the admission requirements,

10:38.470 --> 10:40.040
but if you have the ability

10:40.040 --> 10:41.230
to improve your English further,

10:41.260 --> 10:43.380
it'll definitely help when you intern

10:43.400 --> 10:44.200
at hotels in other countries later.

10:45.220 --> 10:46.790
Got it. Thanks.

10:48.400 --> 10:49.200
Ms. Shen,

10:49.800 --> 10:50.600
could you come out for a moment?

10:53.590 --> 10:54.990
Alright, I'll be in touch with you later.

10:54.990 --> 10:55.710
Thanks for your help.

10:55.920 --> 10:56.590
Alright.

11:04.230 --> 11:05.080
What's the matter?

11:06.680 --> 11:08.110
Are you two-timing?

11:08.510 --> 11:09.110
What?

11:09.630 --> 11:10.870
Who told you that?

11:11.110 --> 11:12.590
Who told us?

11:12.870 --> 11:13.900
So it is true?

11:14.080 --> 11:15.080
No, it's not.

11:16.460 --> 11:17.300
Look for yourself.

11:20.590 --> 11:21.870
The woman in this photo is you.

11:22.920 --> 11:23.920
And the man?

11:24.110 --> 11:25.260
Who is he?

11:26.080 --> 11:27.230
No wonder every time

11:27.230 --> 11:28.640
I bring up Yan Heng lately,

11:28.870 --> 11:30.350
you avoid eye contact.

11:35.590 --> 11:36.830
I broke up with Yan Heng.

11:41.620 --> 11:43.930
We actually split up a while ago.

11:44.800 --> 11:46.710
I just haven't found the right time to tell you both.

11:47.200 --> 11:48.070
Why?

11:48.200 --> 11:49.050
Why did you break up?

11:49.440 --> 11:50.590
Did he treat you badly?

11:52.800 --> 11:55.280
It's just that we were together for too long,

11:55.710 --> 11:56.700
and our feelings faded.

11:58.510 --> 11:59.160
Besides,

12:00.320 --> 12:01.960
he's been abroad all this time,

12:02.710 --> 12:03.830
and we barely had

12:04.320 --> 12:05.840
any common topics to talk about.

12:06.040 --> 12:07.280
So we just ended on great terms.

12:07.990 --> 12:09.380
Why didn't you tell us?

12:09.480 --> 12:11.080
Doesn't it feel suffocating to keep it all to yourself?

12:12.160 --> 12:15.160
Actually, there's something else I want to tell you.

12:15.350 --> 12:17.000
What is it? Just say it.

12:18.710 --> 12:19.990
I want to study abroad

12:20.320 --> 12:21.230
in Switzerland

12:22.110 --> 12:23.440
for a master's in hotel management.

12:26.410 --> 12:28.320
Shen Xifan, this is too sudden.

12:29.050 --> 12:30.960
I wanted to go right after graduating college,

12:31.470 --> 12:32.990
but back then,

12:32.990 --> 12:35.280
the internship opportunity at Gunan Huating was too valuable to pass up.

12:35.510 --> 12:39.080
Plus, Yan Heng didn't agree with it either.

12:41.080 --> 12:42.200
Even if we agree now,

12:42.710 --> 12:44.320
you can't just quit your job, right?

12:44.590 --> 12:45.920
With how busy you are,

12:45.920 --> 12:48.560
applying for a study-abroad program requires a ton of paperwork,

12:48.560 --> 12:49.320
not to mention the English exams.

12:49.320 --> 12:49.890
Yes.

12:50.160 --> 12:51.160
Do you even have time?

12:51.190 --> 12:52.190
Do you have the energy for it?

12:52.510 --> 12:53.680
I've already passed my IELTS.

12:56.390 --> 12:59.150
And I've hired a study-abroad agency

12:59.170 --> 13:00.420
to help with my application materials.

13:00.590 --> 13:01.590
If everything goes smoothly,

13:01.590 --> 13:03.040
I can leave in February.

13:03.280 --> 13:04.630
So you've already decided without telling us first.

13:04.630 --> 13:05.280
No.

13:06.230 --> 13:07.160
Think about it.

13:07.600 --> 13:09.010
You're already 27.

13:09.470 --> 13:11.280
By the time you return, how old will you be?

13:12.130 --> 13:12.890
Let me ask you this.

13:13.630 --> 13:14.680
Once you're done with your studies,

13:15.110 --> 13:16.030
will you come back?

13:17.010 --> 13:18.680
If you do,

13:18.680 --> 13:20.350
you'll have to start job-hunting.

13:21.030 --> 13:22.750
At your age, companies will consider

13:22.990 --> 13:26.040
your relationship status, marriage plans,

13:26.040 --> 13:27.510
whether you'll have kids,

13:27.620 --> 13:30.170
maternity leave, parental leave—

13:30.630 --> 13:31.920
I know exactly how these things work.

13:33.040 --> 13:33.560
Also...

13:33.560 --> 13:34.120
Enough.

13:38.970 --> 13:39.850
I get it.

14:18.110 --> 14:19.470
Why are you sitting here alone?

14:21.350 --> 14:22.420
What's got you brooding?

14:24.830 --> 14:26.160
I'm not brooding.

14:26.560 --> 14:27.710
I'm just thinking.

14:28.680 --> 14:30.710
If you keep pressing like that, even if you punch through
the Danzhong acupoint, it still won't work.

14:34.920 --> 14:36.200
Come on, let's get some late-night snacks.

14:38.400 --> 14:39.800
But I just had dinner.

14:40.440 --> 14:41.510
Trust me.

14:41.710 --> 14:42.710
The food I'm taking you to eat

14:42.710 --> 14:44.200
will clear everything up.

14:45.930 --> 14:46.540
Let's go.

14:48.990 --> 14:50.350
The spicy hot pot is ready.

14:50.350 --> 14:51.080
Thank you.

14:51.080 --> 14:51.750
Be careful, it's hot.

14:53.870 --> 14:54.710
Such a big bowl.

15:03.630 --> 15:05.080
You should avoid spicy food while taking herbal medicine.

15:05.630 --> 15:08.280
Then what's the point of having a spicy hot pot if it's not even spicy?

15:08.510 --> 15:09.320
Don't rush.

15:09.320 --> 15:10.280
Try the broth first.

15:11.160 --> 15:11.790
Give it a taste.

15:20.290 --> 15:20.770
How is it?

15:22.510 --> 15:23.960
This white broth is so good.

15:25.990 --> 15:26.870
Dr. He,

15:27.080 --> 15:28.320
do you need

15:28.320 --> 15:30.440
a really high degree to study medicine?

15:31.080 --> 15:31.920
For the most part, yes.

15:32.660 --> 15:33.990
Would your family

15:34.080 --> 15:35.630
support you studying for so long?

15:38.740 --> 15:39.900
Why are you suddenly asking me this?

15:41.280 --> 15:42.870
I'm thinking about studying abroad.

15:46.750 --> 15:47.590
Actually,

15:47.590 --> 15:48.830
ever since I was a child,

15:48.830 --> 15:50.510
I've followed a set path—

15:50.990 --> 15:52.160
I've been listening to my parents

15:52.160 --> 15:53.560
getting into a local university,

15:53.560 --> 15:55.920
majoring in management as they wanted,

15:55.920 --> 15:58.080
and now, securing a stable job.

15:58.920 --> 16:00.200
But to be honest,

16:00.400 --> 16:02.160
I feel really lost.

16:03.670 --> 16:04.930
I want to study abroad.

16:05.090 --> 16:06.980
I want to go out and see the world.

16:07.010 --> 16:08.110
Only then will I really know

16:08.110 --> 16:09.400
what I want.

16:10.170 --> 16:12.220
But after discussing it with my family,

16:12.250 --> 16:14.290
they brought up so many practical concerns,

16:14.710 --> 16:16.300
and now

16:16.330 --> 16:17.560
I'm starting to waver.

16:21.750 --> 16:22.470
What?

16:23.040 --> 16:25.970
Do you also think I shouldn't go?

16:27.090 --> 16:27.780
No,

16:28.830 --> 16:30.680
I just thought of a friend of mine.

16:31.160 --> 16:32.630
She also studied abroad.

16:33.440 --> 16:36.470
She knew exactly what she wanted,

16:36.830 --> 16:38.680
so she left without hesitation.

16:39.870 --> 16:41.110
That's amazing.

16:42.040 --> 16:43.230
I envy her.

16:43.960 --> 16:44.870
Everyone goes through

16:44.870 --> 16:46.320
a phase like this—

16:46.710 --> 16:48.270
feeling lost, feeling unsure.

16:48.300 --> 16:49.180
It's completely normal.

16:50.200 --> 16:51.200
I really admire you.

16:52.130 --> 16:53.160
You've been working for so long,

16:53.190 --> 16:54.520
yet you haven't let the pressure

16:54.540 --> 16:55.940
crush you into staying in place.

16:56.110 --> 16:58.150
You still have your own curiosity and passion.

16:58.360 --> 16:59.150
That's rare.

16:59.800 --> 17:00.830
Are you serious?

17:00.850 --> 17:01.640
Yes.

17:06.030 --> 17:07.160
To be honest,

17:07.510 --> 17:08.880
when I was in school,

17:08.880 --> 17:10.310
I also had huge conflicts

17:10.310 --> 17:12.160
with my family over my major.

17:13.710 --> 17:15.420
My mom and grandfather practiced TCM,

17:15.450 --> 17:16.579
while my dad was a Western doctor.

17:16.960 --> 17:18.200
And they had major disagreements

17:18.200 --> 17:20.270
on whether I should study

17:20.290 --> 17:21.569
Chinese or Western medicine.

17:24.119 --> 17:26.430
So why did you choose TCM in the end?

17:29.710 --> 17:30.660
Because of my mom.

17:38.160 --> 17:38.990
She

17:40.600 --> 17:41.880
passed away from breast cancer.

17:47.090 --> 17:50.290
Before she died, she suffered terribly

17:50.360 --> 17:51.550
from the side effects of chemotherapy.

17:52.640 --> 17:53.480
But Chinese medicine

17:53.510 --> 17:54.840
can help alleviate that suffering.

17:55.360 --> 17:57.120
So I chose TCM.

17:59.550 --> 18:00.710
It created a huge rift

18:00.710 --> 18:02.070
between me and my dad,

18:02.710 --> 18:03.600
but

18:05.550 --> 18:06.750
in the end, I found a career

18:06.750 --> 18:07.840
I truly love.

18:11.840 --> 18:12.840
I can already picture it.

18:12.840 --> 18:13.990
In a dozen years,

18:14.250 --> 18:15.690
I'll become like my grandfather—

18:15.720 --> 18:18.000
a contented old TCM physician,

18:18.750 --> 18:20.160
mentoring students, savoring tea,

18:20.160 --> 18:21.840
and enjoying a life of quiet fulfillment.

18:26.310 --> 18:27.470
But back to you,

18:28.200 --> 18:29.710
you have two choices

18:29.710 --> 18:30.680
in front of you now.

18:31.170 --> 18:33.240
Either follow their path for a stable life,

18:33.510 --> 18:35.220
or take a leap and try something new.

18:37.710 --> 18:38.310
Look at me.

18:38.710 --> 18:40.880
Working in the oncology department, I meet many patients every day.

18:41.700 --> 18:42.660
Before the end of their lives,

18:42.680 --> 18:43.930
they always count the regrets

18:43.960 --> 18:44.960
they've had in this life.

18:46.160 --> 18:46.960
That's why I think

18:47.240 --> 18:49.850
you should go for it.

18:50.100 --> 18:51.410
What if it turns out to be everything you hoped for?

18:53.000 --> 18:54.000
Well…

18:54.020 --> 18:55.790
Thank you for your guidance, Dr. He.

18:55.820 --> 18:57.050
What guidance?

18:58.160 --> 18:59.510
My 31 years of life

18:59.510 --> 19:00.960
have just boiled down to nothing but a bowl of chicken soup.

19:01.370 --> 19:02.400
Try it, don't be shy.

19:02.970 --> 19:05.300
Alright, then I'll take a big sip.

19:10.550 --> 19:11.180
Tastes good, right?

19:12.160 --> 19:12.960
Not bad.

19:17.510 --> 19:18.200
Dr. He,

19:18.540 --> 19:19.970
you really know how to pick a place.

19:20.310 --> 19:20.880
Right?

19:21.270 --> 19:23.430
Next time you find a good spot, remember to invite me.

19:23.500 --> 19:24.150
Absolutely.

19:37.070 --> 19:37.710
Look.

19:38.030 --> 19:40.070
We often make these little cards

19:40.070 --> 19:41.840
and fold towels

19:41.840 --> 19:43.550
into fun shapes for kids at the hotel.

19:43.890 --> 19:46.000
This way, when they're feeling down,

19:46.030 --> 19:47.160
seeing these will lift their spirits.

19:47.420 --> 19:49.420
No wonder you're so good at origami.

19:51.160 --> 19:51.920
The registration slip.

19:54.600 --> 19:55.840
Now I remember.

19:56.270 --> 19:57.840
I folded it absentmindedly.

20:00.790 --> 20:01.880
Actually,

20:01.880 --> 20:05.030
hotel management has a lot of depth to it.

20:05.470 --> 20:07.600
I remember when I first graduated from university,

20:07.620 --> 20:09.510
one of my mom's colleagues said to her,

20:09.600 --> 20:10.780
"Hey,

20:10.950 --> 20:12.550
how come your daughter graduated from college

20:12.550 --> 20:13.920
just to become a janitor?"

20:14.160 --> 20:15.550
My mom was really upset

20:15.550 --> 20:17.310
and argued with them for a long time.

20:18.070 --> 20:20.070
But she still supported your job,

20:20.070 --> 20:20.640
didn't she?

20:21.790 --> 20:22.920
She did.

20:25.400 --> 20:26.270
So,

20:27.070 --> 20:28.440
you're still quite fortunate.

20:29.900 --> 20:30.820
I can tell.

20:31.450 --> 20:32.610
They all love you very much.

20:54.310 --> 20:55.680
I've thought it through.

20:55.880 --> 20:57.200
I understand your concerns.

20:57.440 --> 20:58.880
This time, I'm applying to

20:58.880 --> 21:00.400
a top-three global university.

21:00.400 --> 21:01.680
It's very challenging,

21:01.880 --> 21:03.330
but I still want to give it a try.

21:03.600 --> 21:05.030
If I fail,

21:05.030 --> 21:07.200
then I'll accept it and let go of the idea.

21:26.470 --> 21:28.320
Why isn't he responding to me?

21:46.280 --> 21:47.810
You should study Western medicine

21:48.070 --> 21:49.270
and pursue clinical work,

21:49.270 --> 21:50.650
step by step.

21:50.680 --> 21:52.810
You just need to follow the path,

21:53.990 --> 21:55.920
and you'll gain success and fame in the future.

22:00.230 --> 22:01.470
All these years,

22:01.490 --> 22:02.660
have you ever cared about me?

22:03.230 --> 22:04.790
When my mother was critically ill,

22:05.640 --> 22:06.400
where were you?

22:14.600 --> 22:15.360
He Suye.

22:33.790 --> 22:34.640
What's wrong?

22:33.900 --> 22:39.630
♫We are miles away♫

22:35.000 --> 22:36.760
I have great news to tell you.

22:37.400 --> 22:38.710
What is it? You seem so happy.

22:40.700 --> 22:42.420
My parents agreed to let me study abroad.

22:43.120 --> 22:44.840
Really? Congratulations then!

22:47.880 --> 22:50.360
I texted you the moment I found out,

22:50.550 --> 22:52.790
but you didn't reply.

22:53.090 --> 22:54.810
I was skateboarding and didn't check my phone.

22:55.740 --> 22:58.020
But if I had seen it,

22:58.050 --> 22:59.130
I definitely would've replied.

23:02.990 --> 23:05.200
Looks like you're too excited to sleep.

23:04.950 --> 23:12.780
♫Away, away, away from me♫

23:08.200 --> 23:08.880
A little.

23:10.550 --> 23:11.200
Well then,

23:11.550 --> 23:12.710
let me take you somewhere.

23:14.130 --> 23:19.090
♫Away from me♫

23:15.230 --> 23:15.750
Let's go.

24:00.610 --> 24:02.690
Want to play some music?

24:09.200 --> 24:10.440
How about

24:11.470 --> 24:12.710
we roll down the window instead?

24:14.130 --> 24:14.970
Sure.

24:39.870 --> 24:47.300
♫So I wait and wander, but the outcome isn't so bad♫

24:43.310 --> 24:45.680
Didn't you say you were taking me out for a ride?

24:45.680 --> 24:47.400
But if there's not even a breeze,

24:47.480 --> 24:54.830
♫Sparrows gather on the windowsill, sunlight streaming through♫

24:47.920 --> 24:49.070
can it really count as a ride?

24:55.020 --> 25:02.640
♫Poets keep altering words to record the fast-changing world♫

25:02.900 --> 25:10.130
♫A fleeting romance, yet you won't give me an answer♫

25:10.700 --> 25:14.300
♫It became brighter because of you♫

25:14.410 --> 25:18.360
♫The world suddenly became so cute♫

25:18.390 --> 25:22.100
♫Maybe I'm too slow to understand♫

25:22.130 --> 25:25.860
♫I can't confess my passionate love to you♫

25:26.050 --> 25:29.860
♫Love is an admiration for beauty♫

25:29.890 --> 25:33.780
♫I've decided to only love you♫

25:33.810 --> 25:35.810
♫My foolishness♫

25:35.830 --> 25:37.670
♫My sincerity♫

25:37.700 --> 25:39.700
♫Only for one person♫

25:42.620 --> 25:48.030
♫Because of you, everything brightens up♫

25:59.960 --> 26:01.960
Why did you bring me to the lakeside?

26:08.070 --> 26:09.960
Back when I first started working,

26:11.790 --> 26:12.920
whenever I felt down

26:13.680 --> 26:14.510
or frustrated,

26:16.230 --> 26:17.840
I'd come here alone.

26:18.310 --> 26:19.310
Take a walk

26:19.880 --> 26:20.710
and space out a bit.

26:25.160 --> 26:26.990
At night, it's especially quiet here,

26:27.440 --> 26:29.680
perfect for sitting alone

26:29.680 --> 26:31.120
and reflecting on your emotions.

26:34.550 --> 26:35.990
But once the sun rises,

26:36.550 --> 26:38.230
this place will become lively again.

26:39.360 --> 26:40.440
It's as if

26:40.950 --> 26:41.600
everything

26:42.270 --> 26:43.960
always returns to its course.

27:02.840 --> 27:03.710
Thank you

27:07.400 --> 27:08.270
for keeping me company

27:10.310 --> 27:11.880
so late at night.

27:23.200 --> 27:24.230
It created a huge rift

27:24.230 --> 27:25.680
between me and my dad,

27:26.440 --> 27:27.120
but...

27:27.840 --> 27:29.990
But she still supported your job,

27:29.990 --> 27:30.750
didn't she?

27:31.310 --> 27:32.360
She did.

27:32.360 --> 27:33.230
So,

27:33.990 --> 27:35.550
you're still quite fortunate.

27:36.790 --> 27:37.750
I can tell.

27:38.550 --> 27:39.790
They all love you very much.

27:55.070 --> 27:55.920
What's wrong?

27:57.380 --> 27:59.210
Is it because of your family?

28:02.510 --> 28:03.440
Well...

28:04.970 --> 28:06.900
Do you want to talk about it?

28:11.160 --> 28:12.920
My situation is quite complicated.

28:13.790 --> 28:15.200
It's not something I can explain in a short time.

28:39.360 --> 28:40.300
He Suye.

28:43.770 --> 28:45.290
Let's watch the sunrise together.

28:52.150 --> 28:52.950
Sure.

28:54.260 --> 28:55.060
Let's watch the sunrise.

28:57.870 --> 28:58.700
Let's watch the sunrise.

29:03.250 --> 29:04.050
It's almost time.

29:06.230 --> 29:07.160
The day is about to break.

29:08.690 --> 29:14.770
♫We are miles away♫

29:31.750 --> 29:32.790
Breakfast is here.

29:34.510 --> 29:36.250
There's one with sugar and one without.

29:36.270 --> 29:37.140
Which one do you want?

29:37.990 --> 29:39.190
I'll have

29:39.610 --> 29:40.370
the one with sugar.

29:39.880 --> 29:47.140
♫Away, away, away from me♫

29:41.270 --> 29:41.960
Here you are.

29:42.470 --> 29:43.310
Thank you.

29:49.180 --> 29:54.140
♫Away from me♫

29:52.440 --> 29:53.440
I didn't expect us

29:54.440 --> 29:56.200
to sit here all night.

29:55.370 --> 30:01.440
♫Away from me♫

30:03.990 --> 30:04.950
The sun is about to rise.

30:05.920 --> 30:10.940
♫We found each other♫

30:06.960 --> 30:08.230
Dawn is about to break.

30:12.150 --> 30:17.500
♫But we've been miles apart♫

30:12.920 --> 30:13.720
Cheers.

30:16.090 --> 30:17.440
Enjoy the sunrise.

30:19.600 --> 30:29.040
♫And I don't think it's fair♫

30:26.750 --> 30:28.710
Look, the sun is coming up.

30:30.960 --> 30:32.270
It's beautiful.

30:34.610 --> 30:43.290
♫And I don't think it's fair♫

30:45.850 --> 30:51.570
[Autumn]

31:03.120 --> 31:04.550
It still feels a bit chilly.

31:04.550 --> 31:06.140
Let's order some bubble tea in a while.

31:06.170 --> 31:06.900
Sounds good.

31:06.920 --> 31:07.430
Alright.

31:35.820 --> 31:36.860
Coming.

31:46.470 --> 31:47.550
I'll be right there.

31:56.800 --> 31:57.560
Manager Shen.

31:59.400 --> 32:01.160
Mr. Ding said he lost something.

32:04.070 --> 32:05.140
Hello, Mr. Ding.

32:05.170 --> 32:07.060
I'm Shen Xifan, the Front Office manager.

32:07.080 --> 32:09.670
I heard you lost something valuable. Is that true?

32:14.030 --> 32:14.600
Hello.

32:15.160 --> 32:15.960
It wasn't lost;

32:16.510 --> 32:17.400
it was stolen.

32:18.710 --> 32:20.440
Could you tell me what exactly is missing?

32:22.300 --> 32:23.220
My wedding ring.

32:23.540 --> 32:24.320
Sorry.

32:24.680 --> 32:25.470
It's my wedding ring.

32:26.120 --> 32:27.960
I woke up this morning, freshened up,

32:27.960 --> 32:29.230
then went to have breakfast.

32:29.470 --> 32:30.400
After that, I took a call

32:30.400 --> 32:31.710
in the garden

32:31.710 --> 32:32.680
before heading back to my room.

32:33.920 --> 32:34.840
That's when the ring disappeared.

32:36.230 --> 32:37.440
During that time,

32:37.440 --> 32:39.640
no one else came into the room,

32:39.640 --> 32:40.550
except for her.

32:41.290 --> 32:42.920
Manager Shen, I didn't steal anything.

32:42.940 --> 32:43.940
I wouldn't dare.

32:45.810 --> 32:47.050
Mr. Ding, please rest assured.

32:47.160 --> 32:49.120
If our staff acted inappropriately

32:49.120 --> 32:50.070
while cleaning,

32:50.070 --> 32:51.510
we will deal with it strictly.

32:52.310 --> 32:52.960
Well,

32:52.960 --> 32:54.990
may I ask where you last saw

32:54.990 --> 32:55.920
your ring?

32:58.400 --> 32:59.710
On the bathroom counter.

33:02.270 --> 33:03.790
Contact the Works Department

33:03.790 --> 33:05.160
and have them dismantle the bathroom pipes

33:05.160 --> 33:05.920
for inspection.

33:06.200 --> 33:07.030
Got it.

33:10.470 --> 33:11.200
Mr. Ding,

33:11.200 --> 33:13.070
may I ask if you were wearing your ring

33:13.070 --> 33:14.270
while having breakfast?

33:15.550 --> 33:17.160
Didn't I already say it?

33:17.160 --> 33:19.600
I freshened up and went to breakfast.

33:19.600 --> 33:20.680
Then, after taking a call

33:20.680 --> 33:22.140
in the garden,

33:22.160 --> 33:23.000
I came back to my room.

33:23.070 --> 33:25.920
When I entered the room, I found the ring was gone.

33:26.550 --> 33:28.460
Do you have any idea how important this ring is to me?

33:28.790 --> 33:29.680
It's not just a symbol

33:29.680 --> 33:31.760
of my love with my wife,

33:31.920 --> 33:34.030
but also a lifelong promise to her.

33:34.030 --> 33:35.710
Never to be lost!

33:36.340 --> 33:38.060
Even the Maybach she gave me

33:38.090 --> 33:39.680
isn't as important as this wedding ring.

33:39.700 --> 33:40.540
You understand, right?

33:41.330 --> 33:43.290
What are you standing there for? Find!

33:44.020 --> 33:45.070
Take good care of Mr. Ding.

34:04.550 --> 34:05.550
The water's gone cold.

34:07.530 --> 34:08.400
My apologies.

35:18.490 --> 35:19.660
I'm very sorry, Mr. Ding,

35:19.690 --> 35:21.730
that we couldn't provide you with the best stay this time.

35:23.720 --> 35:25.950
It's fine. I was just in a bad mood.

35:26.190 --> 35:27.270
Sorry about that.

35:27.300 --> 35:28.290
Not at all.

35:28.890 --> 35:30.290
But that Shen...

35:30.360 --> 35:32.030
Manager Shen

35:32.030 --> 35:33.320
is a good person.

35:33.320 --> 35:34.150
Thank you.

35:34.260 --> 35:36.340
Your recognition is the biggest encouragement for her.

35:36.370 --> 35:37.690
We'll continue improving our service

35:37.710 --> 35:39.020
and hope to provide you

35:39.050 --> 35:40.420
with a perfect stay next time.

35:41.150 --> 35:42.280
The ring has been found.

35:42.280 --> 35:43.870
I'll stay here again next time.

35:44.670 --> 35:45.380
See you.

35:58.260 --> 36:00.140
He obviously lost it himself

36:00.510 --> 36:01.760
and made such a big fuss.

36:02.400 --> 36:03.760
Good thing it was lost in the garden.

36:04.720 --> 36:06.470
If it had been on the way to the restaurant,

36:06.470 --> 36:08.590
we'd have had to turn over the entire hotel lawn.

36:09.630 --> 36:12.590
Also, good thing Manager Shen rushed straight into the rain.

36:12.590 --> 36:14.250
That helped calm Mr. Ding down.

36:15.810 --> 36:17.770
And she actually found the ring.

36:20.840 --> 36:22.110
Where's Manager Shen?

36:22.400 --> 36:24.470
She got drenched, so I told her to shower and change.

36:25.180 --> 36:26.140
She deserves a bonus.

36:27.360 --> 36:28.230
We'll talk about it later.

36:28.250 --> 36:29.730
What do you mean by "we'll talk about it later"?

36:53.280 --> 36:54.240
Xifan.

36:56.030 --> 36:56.840
What's wrong?

36:58.670 --> 37:01.030
I just got my period. My stomach hurts.

37:02.630 --> 37:05.350
So it's the first day, and you got caught in the rain too.

37:05.870 --> 37:07.310
I'll make you some ginger tea.

37:07.480 --> 37:08.440
No need.

37:08.610 --> 37:09.650
Do you have any painkillers?

37:09.670 --> 37:10.720
I've run out of mine.

37:11.470 --> 37:12.800
How about I just request leave for you?

37:12.800 --> 37:13.760
No.

37:13.960 --> 37:14.860
I'll be fine after taking some medicine.

37:15.110 --> 37:15.960
No worries.

37:17.360 --> 37:17.880
Alright.

37:18.080 --> 37:18.770
I'll go get it for you.

38:28.420 --> 38:30.340
You two have such different tastes.

38:30.360 --> 38:32.030
Do you two enjoy eating together?

38:34.150 --> 38:34.990
She's just a friend.

38:37.540 --> 38:38.380
Oh, sorry.

38:39.020 --> 38:41.630
I remember you. You often come to buy my breakfast.

38:42.060 --> 38:43.030
But you've never tried

38:43.030 --> 38:44.070
my spicy hot pot, right?

38:44.070 --> 38:44.440
That's right.

38:44.440 --> 38:45.440
Give it a good try today.

38:45.440 --> 38:46.700
See if it suits your taste.

38:46.910 --> 38:47.680
Take your time.

38:47.700 --> 38:48.740
-Add more if it's not enough.
-Thank you.

38:49.840 --> 38:50.960
This spicy hot pot stall

38:50.960 --> 38:53.000
is the cleanest and most hygienic one on this street.

38:53.030 --> 38:54.000
You should try it.

38:54.860 --> 38:56.860
So you like eating spicy hot pot.

38:58.330 --> 38:59.150
Spicy hot pot

38:59.150 --> 39:00.960
is a very magical food.

39:01.150 --> 39:02.150
As long as the broth is good,

39:02.150 --> 39:03.550
anything you dip in it will be delicious.

39:06.310 --> 39:07.100
What's that look for?

39:08.840 --> 39:09.880
TCM physicians can't skateboard,

39:09.880 --> 39:11.110
and now they can't eat spicy hot pot either?

39:12.880 --> 39:14.110
I just thought,

39:14.130 --> 39:16.900
aren't TCM physicians usually into light flavors?

39:16.930 --> 39:19.120
They probably wouldn't eat something

39:19.150 --> 39:21.060
so salty, oily, and spicy.

39:21.170 --> 39:22.690
Then what should I be eating?

39:22.710 --> 39:23.500
Plain congee with side dishes,

39:23.530 --> 39:24.900
maybe some vegetarian food too.

39:25.170 --> 39:26.960
You sure have a lot of stereotypes about TCM physicians.
